events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Florida Gators

headlines.description: — Nick Saban thinks it might be time for a reckoning like his father used to deliver with a pounding of his hand on the dinner table.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, McClellan lead No. 1 Alabama to 48-14 rout of Mercer

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: — Trevor Lawrence had 412 yards of offense and three touchdowns, Travis Etienne ran for 124 yards and a score and No. 4 Clemson dominated No. 2 Notre Dame 34-10 on Saturday to win its sixth straight Atlantic Coast Conference championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lawrence, No. 4 Clemson rout No. 2 Notre Dame for ACC title

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: — Trey Sermon ran for a school-record 331 yards and two second-half touchdowns Saturday, helping No. 3 Ohio State rally for a 22-10 victory over Northwestern for a fourth consecutive Big Ten championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Ohio St. runs past No. 15 Wildcats for Big Ten crown

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: — Kellen Mond threw for 281 yards and a touchdown and rushed for 59 yards and a score to lead Texas A&M closed its case for inclusion in the College Football Playoff with a 34-13 victory over Tennessee o Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 5 Texas A&M makes last CFP case in 34-13 win vs. Vols

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: — Spencer Rattler threw a 45-yard touchdown to Marvin Mims and also ran for a score as No. 12 Oklahoma won its sixth consecutive Big 12 title, holding on to beat No. 8 Iowa State 27-21 in the conference championship game Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 12 Sooners win 6th B12 title in row, 27-21 over Iowa St

video.headline: Oklahoma holds off Iowa State's comeback bid to win sixth straight Big 12 title

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Oklahoma holds off Iowa State's comeback bid to win sixth straight Big 12 title) 2020/12/19 ESHEET SOTFULL

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: — Cole Smith made a 34-yard field goal as time expired to give No. 6 Cincinnati a 27-24 victory over No. 20 Tulsa on Saturday night in the rainy American Conference Championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Cincinnati beats No. 20 Tulsa in rainy AAC title game

events.name: Boise State Broncos at San José State Spartans

headlines.description: — Nick Starkel completed 32 of 52 passes for 453 yards and three touchdowns to lead No. 25 San Jose State to its first Mountain West Conference championship, 34-20 over Boise State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 25 San Jose State beats Boise State in MWC title game

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Utah Utes

headlines.description: — Ty Jordan ran for 154 yards and three touchdowns to rally Utah to a 45-28 victory over Washington State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah rallies to beat Washington State 45-28 in season finale

events.name: Air Force Falcons at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: — Jakobi Buchanan scored on a 1-yard run with 73 seconds left, and Army rallied past Air Force 10-7 on Saturday to win the Commander-in-Chief’s Trophy for the ninth time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Army beats Air Force 10-7, wins Commander-in-Chief's Trophy

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: — Freshman receiver Kayshon Boutte caught 14 passes for an LSU-record 308 yards receiving, and his third touchdown of the game on a 45-yard catch-and-run with 1:30 remaining lifted the Tigers to a 53-48 victory over Mississippi on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boutte's record day lifts LSU past Ole Miss, 53-48

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: — Will Rogers threw for 295 yards and three touchdowns to lead Mississippi State to a 51-32 victory over Missouri on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rogers throws for 3 TDs, Mississippi St. tops Mizzou 51-32

video.headline: Niko Hea leaps to score a 24-yard TD

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Niko Hea leaps to score a 24-yard TD) 2020/19/20 ESHEET

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: — Collin Larsh kicked a 30-yard field goal in overtime to give Wisconsin a 20-17 victory over Minnesota in the battle for Paul Bunyan’s Axe in the most-played rivalry in the FBS.
headlines.shortLinkText: Larsh's FG lifts Wisconsin past Minnesota 20-17 in OT

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: — Jahan Dotson caught six passes, scored twice and racked up 239 all-purpose yards to lead Penn State to a 56-21 win over Illinois on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dotson paces Penn State in win over Illinois

headlines.description: — Davis Mills threw for 428 yards and three touchdowns, including a 14-yard score to Simi Fehoko in the second overtime as Stanford defeated UCLA 48-47 at the Rose Bowl Saturday night in the season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Road warriors: Stanford caps trip with win over UCLA in 2 OT

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: — Jayden Daniels passed for a touchdown and had two of Arizona State's six rushing touchdowns in the Sun Devils' 46-33 victory over Oregon State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels helps Arizona St. beat Oregon St. 46-33
